Here is a short description of the plugin.  This should be no more than 150 characters.  No markup here.

== Description ==

sshcon lets you manage your ssh connections easily

== Requirements ==

sshpass

== Installation ==


1. Copy "sshcon" and "addresses.in" to /usr/local/bin/ 
2. Make the script executable (chmod +x sshcon)
3. Edit your addresses.in

"addresses.in" has configuration for each ssh connection like below

ALIAS,IP_ADDRESS,USER_NAME,PASSWORD

== Example ==

MYSSH,XX.XX.XX.XX,username,password

== Usage ==

sshcon MYSSH
